{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|又|又|c1=p|c2=p|ls=psc}}<ref>季旭昇撰 『説文新証』 芸文印書館、2014年、210-211頁。<br>徐超 『古漢字通解500例』 中華書局、2022年、243頁。</ref>

Shuowen: two hands, therefore friendship.

===Etymology===
Endoactive derivation of {{och-l|右|right|id=1}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). 

Traditionally considered cognate with {{cog|bo|གྲོགས||friend; companion}} (STEDT). Schuessler rejects this comparison, believing that the ''-r-'' is the initial of a root instead of the ''g-'', and thus that any Chinese cognate of the Tibetan word must also have an initial ''*r'' (which 友 does not have).

